    "Notably, 3D AG-Net trained on nodule-only images, devoid of microenvironment information, achieved an accuracy of 75.61%, sensitivity of 50.00%, and specificity of 88.46%.",
    "It is of significance that this CNN, trained exclusively with nodule images, outperformed the VDT method by 12.98% in terms of accuracy.Note that there are some limitations in the study.",
    "First, we labeled all shrinking-size nodules as benign (negative VDT values based on the modified Schwartz formula).",
    "This assumption could lead to underestimating the VDT prediction accuracy and sensitivity because nodules with a decreased size could still be cancer.",
    "Second, we used a segmentation model to segment lung nodules and then remove the background."
